OL,3,CSignificant shortfalls found in green
OL,4,Cenergy strategy implementation
OL,6,FThe report found that the department
OL,7,Fhas spent an estimated #107 million on
OL,8,Fthe Energy Strategy and related
OL,9,Finitiatives since 2020.
OL,11,FThis includes #85 million on capital
OL,12,Fprojects.
OL,14,FThe report also identifies
OL,15,F"significant flaws" in how the
OL,16,Fstrategy has been implemented,
OL,17,Fparticularly in relation to the
OL,18,Fdepartment's annual Energy Strategy
OL,19,FAction Plans.
